#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:7
msgid "Working with Video Meetings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:13
msgid ""
"In Carbonio, video meetings serve as a fundamental tool for facilitating "
"seamless virtual collaboration. Whether conducting one-on-one discussions"
" or hosting group meetings, video meetings provide a platform for face-"
"to-face interaction, fostering real-time communication and enhancing "
"teamwork."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:15
msgid ""
"Users can easily initiate or join meetings, share screens, and record "
"meetings ensuring efficient collaboration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:18
msgid "Entering Your Personal Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:20
msgid ""
"Every person with an account on Carbonio has a personal room. You can use"
" your room to invite others to meetings, whether they are colleagues with"
" accounts on the same system or external users. To access and enter your "
"personal room, follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:24
msgid ""
"Click PERSONAL ROOM located at the bottom left corner beneath the list of"
" chats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:26
msgid "This action will open your room in another browser tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:29
msgid "Inviting Members to Personal Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:31
msgid "To invite other members to your personal room:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:34 ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:105
msgid ""
"Click the **COPY LINK** located at the bottom left corner beneath the "
"list of chats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:36
msgid ""
"This will copy the link to access your room to your clipboard. You can "
"paste it anywhere (such as in a chat) by right-clicking and selecting "
"**Paste**, or by using the keyboard shortcut CTRL+V on Windows or "
"command+V on macOS. Alternatively, you can enter your room and copy the "
"URL of the page from the address bar of your browser, then send it to "
"your colleagues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:40
msgid "Creating New Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:42
msgid ""
"Rooms are shared spaces where you can hold video meetings and engage in "
"conversations via chat. You can create them based on different topics you"
" want to discuss so that the attendees are informed about the meeting "
"agenda."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:48
msgid ""
"Click **CREATE ROOM** located at the bottom left corner beneath the list "
"of chats. A new window appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:49
msgid "Insert a name for the room in the first field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:50
msgid ""
"If you want to have other moderators who can assist in managing the room "
"alongside you, the main moderator, you can insert your colleagues' emails"
" in the second field and select them from the suggested list. This step "
"is optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:53
msgid ""
"Your room has been successfully created and will be accessible through "
"the **Rooms tab**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:55
msgid ""
"You can use the **ROOM'S LINK** button to copy the room's link. Upon "
"clicking the button, the link will be copied to your clipboard. You can "
"paste it anywhere (such as in a chat) by right-clicking and selecting "
"**Paste**, or by using the keyboard shortcut CTRL+V on Windows or "
"command+V on macOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:57
msgid ""
"If you want to change the link to access the room, click on **RESET "
"LINK**. This action will generate another URL for the room. It is useful "
"in case you have shared the room's link with the wrong person or want to "
"update the link for security reasons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:59
msgid "ou can use the **JOIN ROOM** button to enter the room."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:62
msgid "Entering a Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:67 ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:79
#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:202
msgid "Select the **Rooms tab**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:68 ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:80
#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:203 ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:214
msgid "Click on the desired room from the list to select it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:69 ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:81
msgid "Click ROOM’S LINK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:71
msgid ""
"This action will copy the link to access the room to your clipboard. You "
"can paste it into the address bar of a new browser tab and press Enter. "
"This will direct you to the room."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:74
msgid "Inviting Members to A Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:76
msgid "To invite other members to a room:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:83
msgid ""
"This will copy the link to access the room to your clipboard. You can "
"paste it anywhere (such as in a chat) by right-clicking and selecting "
"**Paste**, or by using the keyboard shortcut CTRL+V on Windows or "
"command+V on macOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:92
msgid ""
"Click on the **INVITE TO YOUR PERSONAL ROOM** button on top of the chat "
"area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:107 ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:135
msgid ""
"This will copy the link to access your room to your clipboard. You can "
"paste it anywhere (such as in a chat) by right-clicking and selecting "
"**Paste**, or by using the keyboard shortcut CTRL+V on Windows or "
"command+V on macOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:112
msgid ""
"When you are in a video meeting, you can turn your webcam or microphone "
"on or off. Here is how: Toggle the microphone or camera icon on the "
"bottom bar inside the meeting room. If you do not see the bottom bar, "
"simply move your mouse cursor to the bottom of the screen, and it will "
"appear."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:119
msgid "Click the blue button in the bottom left corner to open the chat box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:120
msgid "Click the \"i\" icon located at the top right corner of the chat box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:121
msgid "Under the **Recording** section, click **START**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:123
msgid ""
"To stop the video meeting, simply click the **STOP** button. This action "
"will automatically save your recording file into your Files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:128
msgid ""
"To add new members to an ongoing video meeting, you need to send them the"
" link to access the room."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:130
msgid ""
"Here is how: #.      Click the blue button in the bottom left corner to "
"open the chat box. #.      Click the \"i\" icon located at the top right "
"corner of the chat box. #.      Click COPY ROOM’S LINK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:140
msgid ""
"To access the chat box of the room where you are having the video "
"meeting, simply click the blue button in the bottom left corner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:145
msgid "When you are in a video meeting, you can share your screen with attendees."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:147
msgid ""
"Here is how: Click the screen icon on the bottom bar inside the meeting "
"room. If you do not see the bottom bar, simply move your mouse cursor to "
"the bottom of the screen, and it will appear."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:149
msgid ""
"You have three options to choose from: •       Your browser tab. •       "
"A specific window. •       Entire screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:154
msgid "Select the desired option and then click **Share**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:157
msgid "Toggling Grid View and Cinema View During a Video Meeting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:159
msgid ""
"When you are in a video meeting, you can change the viewing option to "
"different available modes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:161
msgid "Cinema mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:162
msgid "Grid mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:164
msgid ""
"In cinema mode, the speaker appears in the biggest box, while others are "
"displayed in smaller boxes in the right corner. In grid mode, all "
"attendees are shown together in the center part simultaneously. To switch"
" between these modes, click on the icon with boxes inside located on the "
"bottom bar. If you do not see the bottom bar inside the meeting room, "
"simply move your mouse cursor to the bottom of the screen, and it will "
"appear."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:168
msgid "Adding Virtual Background to Your Video During a Video Meeting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:170
msgid ""
"When you are in a video meeting, you have the option to change the "
"background of your video feed, allowing other attendees to see a "
"different background behind you. To do so: click on the circular icon "
"located on the bottom bar. If you do not see the bottom bar inside the "
"meeting room, simply move your mouse cursor to the bottom of the screen, "
"and it will appear."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:181
msgid ""
"As the moderator of a meeting room, you can mute an attendee's microphone"
" individually. To do so, simply hover your cursor over the video feed of "
"the attendee and click on the microphone icon located at the top right of"
" their video feed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:184
msgid "Resetting the Meeting Room's Link"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:186
msgid ""
"It is useful in case you have shared the room's link with the wrong "
"person or want to update the link for security reasons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:188
msgid ""
"If you want to change the link to access the room: #.      Select the "
"**Chats feature** from your left sidebar. #.      Select the **Rooms "
"tab**. #.      Click on the desired room from the list to select it. #."
"      Click on the **RESET LINK**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:194
msgid "This action will generate another URL for the room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:204
msgid "Click on DELETE ROOM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:210
msgid "To Add a moderator in a meeting room:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:213
msgid "Select the Rooms tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:215
msgid "Click on ADD MODERATOR. A new window appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../videomeetings/toc.rst:216
msgid ""
"Begin typing the email address of the new moderator and select it from "
"the suggested list."
msgstr ""

